.SH "NAME"
lsmod \- Show the status of modules in the Linux Kernel
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.HP \w'\fBlsmod\fR\ 'u
\fBlsmod\fR
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.PP
\fBlsmod\fR
is a trivial program which nicely formats the contents of the
/proc/modules, showing what kernel modules are currently loaded\&.
